SOC107 - Privilege Escalation Detected
Summary:
---

On January 31, 2021, at 04:20 PM UTC, the MSOC Security team received an alert titled “SOC107 – Privilege Escalation Detected.” The alert was triggered when user Richard from the Accounting department was observed downloading a suspicious file named "JuicyPotato.exe" on host RichardPRD with IP 172[.]16[.]17[.]45.

Further investigation revealed that the user accessed the URL Request URL: hxxp[://]andaluciabeach[.]net/image/network[.]exe via a GET request, resulting in the download of a malicious file named JuicyPotato.exe. The file was executed by EQNEDT32.EXE, a process commonly exploited in Microsoft Office-based privilege escalation attacks, and its parent process was excel.exe.

An OSINT check confirmed that the file hash 808502752ca0492aca995e9b620d507b was malicious. The destination IP 5[.]135[.]143[.]133 was also identified as malicious.

I have revoked all active user sessions and disconnected the host from the network pending further remediations.


